node.text: Will the Circle Be Unbroken.  Big shout out to these beautiful souls for helping me get ready for my Grand Ole Opry debut.  I had the time of my life and I had to pinch myself this mornin.  Charlie,  I love your new song Believe in Love.  It’s amazing

node.text: I have so much to learn from my adored friend @brandicarlile, and I think that her struggle with a faith that once rejected her would provide comfort to many other souls as well. She learned to see past all the narrow peripherals of that faith to find and embrace its fundamental spirit.  She lives by that spirit today, and her music and her thrilling voice are an invitation to others to share her peace.  Please visit her page and grab your copy of Broken Horses which is out now.  You can also find our whole conversation where this video clip was taken.  Love. Light. Leslie. @thetanyatucker

node.text: “At times of stress, at times of peace, I would recite the old words and hum the sturdy tunes, and the weariness of years, the burdens of time would melt away. I found myself, as I find myself to this day, revived and renewed, if only for the length of a few beloved verses. But how welcome that brief restoration of a child’s fleeting and marvelous belief can be. “. Thank ALL of you for taking this journey with me.  @weareplatoon @travishoward @dannymyrick @dollyparton @eddievedder @chrisstapleton @morganwithane @thetanyatucker @brandicarlile @tjosborne @katiepruittmusic @ashleymcbryde @charlieworsham

node.text:
Don’t forget to listen to our first two songs on our album Company’s Comin’. Also, you can preorder the whole album before it comes out on April 2. 
I have the most amazing artists joining me — even Dolly Parton and Eddie Vedder.  Please check it out with the link in my bio.

node.text: Happy 4th of July everyone.  I’ve been quiet for awhile but @lisarinna’s dance video kicked me into gear.  Whatever you do this holiday weekend, make sure you “dance like nobody is watching.” Love. Light. Leslie.

node.text: I had the honor to make a new friend today. Her name is @jalaiah and she is a beautiful force and a lovely little lady.  She is a dancer and one of the best I’ve ever seen.  She invented a dance called the Renegade and it went viral on social media. Here’s the problem — she never received her due credit because folks never mentioned her.  Help me shine a light on a lady that already shines bright.  Go Jalaiah.

node.text: Hey @nordstrom, thanks for inviting me to celebrate Pride with y’all this year in the West Village (NYC). I had a blast.  I just want to remind everyone what Oscar Wilde once said, “Be yourself, everyone else is already taken.” Love. Light. Leslie.

node.text: My dear friend @brandicarlile sang one of my favorite songs the other day.  I sang the same song last year at a dinner party.  I merged the two videos together —— we sound good y’all.  Love you @brandicarlile and @thetanyatucker
